<content>
    <chapter line="1">3. Dvattiṃsākāro</chapter>
    <paragraph line="2">Atthi <pageBreak edition="Vipassana Research Institut" number="0.0003" /> imasmiṃ kāye –</paragraph>
    <gatha1 line="3">Kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco,</gatha1>
    <gatha2 line="4">Maṃsaṃ <alternatives line="3" extra="" separator="true"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">nhāru</alternative><alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">nahāru</alternative><alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">nahāru</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">nahārū</alternative><alternative source-abbr="kaṃ." source="kaṃ.">nahārū</alternative></alternatives>  <alternatives line="12" extra="" separator="false"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">aṭṭhi</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">aṭṭhī</alternative><alternative source-abbr="kaṃ" source="kaṃ">aṭṭhī</alternative></alternatives>  aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ,</gatha2>
    <gatha3 line="5">Hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ,</gatha3>
    <gatha2 line="6">Antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ matthaluṅgaṃ <note>( ) sabbattha natthi, aṭṭhakathā ca dvattiṃsasaṅkhyā ca manasi kātabbā</note>,</gatha2>
    <gatha3 line="7">Pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo,</gatha3>
    <gathalast line="8">Assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā <alternatives line="23" extra="" separator="false"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">muttanti</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">muttaṃ, matthake matthaluṅganti</alternative></alternatives> .</gathalast>
    <centered line="9">Dvattiṃsākāro niṭṭhito.</centered>
  </content>
